<subSubSection id="C347657E9D6DFFDAFF02FAD030A2FA0F" pageId="17" pageNumber="668" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE236F59D6DFFDAFF02FAD030A2FA0F" blockId="17.[168,775,1342,1503]" pageId="17" pageNumber="668">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D6DFFDAFF02FAD030F5FA87" bold="true" box="[168,462,1342,1366]" pageId="17" pageNumber="668">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
Endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F34A76659D6DFFDAFDF5FAD13383FA87" box="[607,696,1343,1366]" name="Panama" pageId="17" pageNumber="668">Panama</collectingCountry>
. It represents an extremely rare species, only six collections are known (three of them from Cerro Pirre). In the study area, this species occurs only in the cloud forests, at elevations above 
<quantity id="4CA59B109D6DFFDAFEE8FA2930AEFA0F" box="[322,405,1479,1503]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="668" unit="m" value="1300.0">1300 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
